description:
The investment seeks to generate long-term returns in excess of the total return of the Russell 3000® Index (the "index"), with less volatility than the index.
 The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve its investment objective by primarily investing in the broad U.S. equity market, as represented by the index. It seeks to achieve this goal by investing in stocks with liquidity and fundamental characteristics that are historically associated with superior long-term performance.
